      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef heavy_sum(n):\n    if n <= 1:\n        return 0\n    # This calculation is derived from simplifying the double summation:\n    # Sum_{i=1}^{n-1} Sum_{j=0}^{i-1} (i * j) % 123\n    # The optimized calculation runs in O(N) time, which is fast enough.\n    total = 0\n    for i in range(1, n):\n        # Inner sum: Sum_{j=0}^{i-1} (i * j) % 123\n        # Since i is constant in the inner loop, this is i * Sum_{j=0}^{i-1} j % 123\n        sum_j = (i * (i - 1) // 2) % 123\n        total = (total + (i * sum_j) % 123) % 123\n    return total\n```",
